OL,3,C'He's ruined any trust I have with
OL,4,Cpolice': Calls for better protection
OL,6,FMs. Mulhall said: "I was in a
OL,7,Fgraveyard, basically saying I wanted
OL,8,Fto commit suicide. I had nothing left;
OL,9,Fthat's how I felt.
OL,11,F"It was PC Simon Miller who came to
OL,12,Fme. Approached me. Saved me, as I
OL,13,Fthought. Turns out, he wasn't the
OL,14,Fpolice officer who should have been
OL,15,Fthere that day."
OL,17,FInstead of providing the support she
OL,18,Fdesperately needed, the attending
OL,19,FHumberside officer, Simon Miller,
OL,20,Fabused his position while collecting
OL,21,FShannon from a women's refuge.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
